# Loadout — Environment Variables

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE_URL (required for persistent data storage)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Without this, data is stored in a temporary location (/tmp)
# and will be LOST whenever the server restarts.
#
# For local development (SQLite):
DATABASE_URL="file:./prisma/dev.db"
#
# For production on Vercel — use a PostgreSQL provider such as:
#   • Neon       (https://neon.tech)      — free tier available
#   • Supabase   (https://supabase.com)   — free tier available
#   • Railway    (https://railway.app)    — free tier available
#
# Example PostgreSQL URL:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:5432/loadout?sslmode=require"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JWT_SECRET (required in production)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A long random string used to sign authentication tokens.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_SECRET="loadout-dev-secret-change-in-production"
